Rick Sacks leads The Array Ensemble in a program of pieces written for Arraymusic. The title for the concert is also the sub-title of Rudolf Komorous’ piece Dame’s Rocket (The Rainbow of Forgetting 2). Its combination of evocative beauty and elusive obscurity is very much in keeping with Komorous’ estetiku divnosti, his “aesthetic of curious things” / “aesthetic of the strange” / “aesthetic of the wonderful.” Komorous developed this philosophy with a group of like-minded artists in Prague during the late 1950s. In an interview he explained that "the group's main philosophy was that things should somehow be driven on the edge—on that edge when you cannot really recognize what's serious, what's not serious; you know, what's true, what's not true; what's sort of from life and what is a sheer imagination. Simply that edge—because we thought that on that edge real things happen.” This concert brings together six extremely different—wonderfully different—pieces of music. Yet all this music, in utterly distinct ways, is driven on the edge, moves along and inhabits that edge, and encourages the listener to join it there.
PROGRAMME

Martin Arnold: (Damper) Coaster (2000)

Linda Bouchard: Ductwork (1997)

Rudolf Komorous: Dame's Rocket (the rainbow of forgetting 2) (1991)

Marjan Mozetich: Time to Leave (1997)

John Mark Sherlock: Necklace (1997)

Linda Catlin Smith: Stare at the River (2010)
title: Rainbow of Forgetting

They are called “sister ferments.” Raw vinegar and kombucha ferment very similarly, the latter being effervescent and slightly sweet. One of the most popular among the fermented beverages, kombucha is a sugar-sweetened tea fermented by a culture of living organisms called a SCOBY (symbiotic colony of bacteria and yeast.) This tonic is akin to raw vinegar.

Raw vinegar is used to aid detoxification, to add as a sour flavor in foods, for cleaning and much more. It alkalizes our bodies and can be used as a remedy for a wide array of ailments or conditions. An acetic acid ferment, raw vinegar is simple to make. Yet commercially, it is almost always deprived of its live culture benefits.

We will learn about home brewing kombucha for beginners, plus dive into the art of second fermentation, techniques and methods to get your brew at its best. We will also learn how to make raw apple cider vinegar, which requires nothing more than apples and pure water. Live kombucha cultures will be available for you to take home, plus home brewing instructions to get your first batch going. Participants will also be able to taste all of our fermented food and beverages, all made locally. Space is limited, so be sure to sign up by February 13, 2017.
title: Kombucha and Raw Apple Cider Vinegar Workshop.

This March, Women Who Whiskey is turning six! As a way to support women (who make this group possible), and as a thank you for sticking with us for over half a decade, we are making our birthday celebration all about International Women's Day! Every March, the world gets together to celebrate and empower women; this year, we want to join in, and we want you to join us!

On Saturday, March 11 from 1-3 PM, join us for a celebration of International Women's Day and Women Who Whiskey's birthday with a special event to benefit the girls & women of New York City. Event proceeds and donations will support The Bowery Mission recovery programs for women and Big Brothers Big Sisters NYC's girls' programs.

     Date: Saturday, March 11, 2017

     Time: 1-3 PM

     Location: Tanner Smith's, 204 West 55th St, NY 10019 (between Broadway & 7th Ave)

Tickets: $35, includes Woodford Reserve tasting, 2 Woodford Reserve cocktails, light bites, sweet treats, photo booth, live music, make up bar, oxygen bar, personalized haikus, raffle prizes and a costume contest, cocktail specials, and more! Ticket proceeds will go to support The Bowery Mission and Big Brothers Big Sisters NYC, our partner organizations for this event.

In addition to all the fun activities and booths we'll have for you, we'll also have some raffles and contests where you can win Woodford Reserve cocktail kits, hand-crafted hats, and more! Details below!

This event is open to ladies and gentlemen, so bring your family, friends & lovers!

Costume Contest

To honor the great women of the past - including whiskey women! - who fought for the world we live in today, we invite you to come dressed up as your favorite historical bad ass women. It could be anyone from Rosie the Riveter to Norma Ray, fighting for labor rights; from Dorothy Parker to Zelda Fitzgerald, wielding their wit and their writing; from Rosa Parks to Coretta Scott King, fighting for racial justice; from Eleanor Roosevelt to Jackie Kennedy, using the White House as a national podium. Your imagination is the only limitation! We invite you to be creative and sassy! Three winners will receive a handmade custom cloche hat from Christina's Millinery.

Donation Raffle

In addition to donating proceeds from the event to our partner organizations, we'll also be collecting donation items on their behalf! For Big Brothers Big Sister, please bring new, unused/unopened school supply items, such as pens, pencils, notebooks, backpacks, etc. In 2016, NYC became the first city in the US to provide free hygienic products to girls and women in schools and shelters, but they still have a lot of other needs that we can help with! For the Bowery Mission, we'll be collecting new, unused/unopened travel-sized toiletries such as soap, deodorant, shaving cream, toothpaste, toothbrushes, shampoo/conditioner, etc. Every donation item will receive a raffle ticket, so the more you bring, the better your odds! If you can't bring a donation item, but still want to support these organizations, we are offering the option to purchase tickets that include general admission plus a $10 donation to the organization of your choice. If you purchase one of these tickets, you will receive one raffle ticket and be eligible to win a prize, as if you had brought a donation item. Three winners will receive a Woodford Reserve Cocktail Kit, including a mini bottle of Woodford Reserve, Vermouth, Bitters, a mug, and Cocktail Kingdom barware.

We are so excited about this special event, and hope you can join us to help support the girls & women in our community! The space is large, so feel free to invite all family, friends & lovers!

Ladies & Gentlemen Welcome!

description:
These films all explore the theme of expression. They show the subjects expressing themselves in different ways; for Nthako in G-Face, hip-hop is his means of expression while Brainwash expresses a clear message about working entirely without dialogue. The films each offer suggestions about the significance of one's identity and how the individual manifests itself.

What happens in your brain.. (Zora Rux. Germany)

 A surreal trip into the world of an extremely long german word.

Whining Low (Sergio Zaciu.	United States)

Svetlana, an undocumented citizen from Russia, pursues a distant 'American dream' in rural Texas. She works the graveyard shift at the local gas station, trying to stay away from the attention of the police. One evening she sees an opportunity of escape; but is her perception of the situation correct?

Brainwash (Hannah Gautrey. UK)

Just a group of normal people on a nine-to-five working day. Entirely without dialogue, this film brings into question what the average person gains from working and who is really benefitting from their labour.

G Face (Bafana Gedion Monyamane, South Africa)

Thabo “ G Face” Nthako is a hip-hop artist from a small mining town in South Africa. His lyrics focus on motivating others and on social issues, but he lacks wide recognition - this documentary seeks to find out why.

description:

Hamish Fint, a crotchety old man used to a life of seclusion inside his submarine balanced precariously atop a mountain, struggles to maintain equilibrium when an unwelcome visiting seagull rocks his world.

Content warnings: spanking

description:
A free course showing how process integration techniques and NRCan's INTEGRATION software can be used to identify energy efficiency opportunities in complex industrial plants.

Process integration analyzes the energy use of a plant or process as a whole, rather than solely considering each equipment item or energy system independently. As such, it can determine the thermodynamically minimum consumption of hot and cold utilities necessary for the plant, and provide insight into design or retrofit options that may attain these targets. Energy savings ranging from 10 to 30% are typical, even in up-to-date plants that have been subject to conventional energy audit methods, resulting in cost savings, greenhouse gas emissions reductions, water savings, and increased production throughput.

INTEGRATION software, an easy-to-use but powerful tool available for free from NRCan, assists in the application of process integration techniques to complex industrial plants with high heat requirements. INTEGRATION also includes modules for quickly evaluating heat recovery opportunities for boilers, refrigeration systems, and compression systems.

Duration: approximately 3.5 hours

Participants will be given an evaluation version of the INTEGRATION software that they can install on a laptop for use during the course.

For other free introductory courses, see http://www.rerinfo.ca/RETScreenTraining.html
title: Industrial Energy Efficiency and Process Integration, Toronto, March 14

7:00 pm - 'Killer' pre-show & lobby pop-up featuring local artists! 8:00 pm - Movie starts!The Honeymoon Killers is a sordid masterpiece - written and directed by Leonard Kastle and inspired by the true story of 'The Lonely Hearts Killers", a dangerous duo named Raymond Ferandez and Martha Jule Beck, who murdered as many as 20 women between 1947 and 1949, by answering lonely hearts ads in newspapers. Shirley Stoler stars as Martha Beck, an embittered nurse who lives with her senile mother, and has long since abandoned the idea that she could ever find love. When Martha's friend Bunny submits her to the 'lonely hearts' club, she receives a letter from the sultry Ray Fernandez, who she immediately becomes enamoured with. After she eventually moves to New York to live with Ray, she learns that he routinely seduces women and steals their money, but Martha loves him anyway. Matters escalate as the two become more and more intertwined, leaving a bloody, chaotic mess along the way. Ain't love grand?
